@startuml
title Public Resume Processing — AI-Orchestrated, Event-Driven, Real-Time UX
autonumber

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FDF6E3
skinparam noteBorderColor #657B83
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam participantPadding 12
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor "Candidate FE\n(Public Angular)" as FE
participant "Gateway\n(YARP)" as GW
participant "Monolith API\n(System of Record)" as MON
database "Monolith DB\n(SQL Server)" as MSQL
participant "Outbox Processor" as OBX
participant "AI Service v2\n(Orchestrator)" as AI
participant "OpenAI API" as OAI
database "Embeddings DB\n(PostgreSQL + pgvector)" as PG

== SYNCHRONOUS PATH — Fast User Acknowledgment ==

FE -> GW: Upload resume
activate GW
GW -> MON: POST /api/resumes
activate MON

MON -> MSQL: INSERT Resume + INSERT Outbox
activate MSQL
note right of MSQL
Atomic transaction boundary:
- Persist resume metadata
- Write outbox event
Single commit ensures consistency
end note
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MSQL

MON --> GW: 201 Created
deactivate MON
GW --> FE: Upload accepted
deactivate GW

note over FE
User receives immediate response.
System prioritizes UX latency over full processing.
end note

== ASYNCHRONOUS PATH — Event-Driven Processing ==

OBX -> AI: resume.uploaded (via Dapr pub/sub)
activate AI

note over AI
End-to-end pipeline (~19s):
- Phase 1: Contact parse (~1s)
- Phase 2: 5 parallel sections (~9s)
- Embeddings (~0.5s)
- 4 parallel match explanations (~6s)
end note

== Phase 1 — Contact Info (Sequential, Fast) ==

AI -> OAI: Parse contact info only
activate OAI
note right of OAI
~1.3s — minimal extraction
name, email, phone, links
end note
OAI --> AI: contact JSON
deactivate OAI

AI -> MON: Save contact section
activate MON
MON -> MSQL: MERGE into parsed content
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MON

AI -> FE: SignalR ResumeSectionParsed ("contact")

note over FE
Contact info appears immediately (~1s).
UI kicks remaining sections to "parsing".
end note

== Phase 2 — 5 Parallel Section Parses ==

note over AI, OAI
5 independent LLM calls via Task.WhenAll:
skills, workHistory, education, certifications, projects
Wall time = slowest section (~8-9s)
end note

par skills
AI -> OAI: Parse summary + skills
OAI --> AI: skills JSON
else workHistory
AI -> OAI: Parse work history
OAI --> AI: workHistory JSON
else education
AI -> OAI: Parse education
OAI --> AI: education JSON
else certifications
AI -> OAI: Parse certifications
OAI --> AI: certifications JSON
else projects
AI -> OAI: Parse projects
OAI --> AI: projects JSON
end

loop each completed section
AI -> MON: Save section
MON -> MSQL: MERGE into parsed content
MON --> AI: OK
AI -> FE: SignalR ResumeSectionParsed (section)
end

note over FE
UI progressively hydrates
as each section completes.
end note

AI -> MON: All sections completed
activate MON
MON -> MSQL: Mark resume fully parsed + INSERT Outbox (resume.parsed)
MSQL --> MON: committed
deactivate MON

== Phase 3 — Embeddings Generation ==

note over AI
Triggered by resume.parsed event (via Dapr pub/sub)
end note

AI -> OAI: Generate 3 embeddings (parallel batch)
activate OAI
note right of OAI
~0.5s parallel batch
full + skills + experience vectors
text-embedding-3-small (1536-dim)
end note
OAI --> AI: 3 vectors
deactivate OAI

AI -> PG: Upsert resume embeddings
activate PG
PG --> AI: stored
deactivate PG

AI -> FE: SignalR ResumeEmbedded

== Phase 4 — Match Explanations (Parallel, Fire-and-Forget) ==

AI -> PG: Find top 10 matching jobs (pgvector cosine similarity)
activate PG
note right of PG
Weighted composite scoring in DB:
40% skills + 40% experience + 20% full
ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT 10
end note
PG --> AI: top 10 job IDs + scores
deactivate PG

AI -> MON: Fetch job details (batch)
activate MON
MON --> AI: job titles, descriptions, qualifications
deactivate MON

note over AI, OAI
4 parallel LLM calls (batches of 3 jobs each)
Wall time = slowest batch (~6-7s)
end note

par batch 1 (jobs 1-3)
AI -> OAI: Generate explanations
OAI --> AI: explanations JSON
else batch 2 (jobs 4-6)
AI -> OAI: Generate explanations
OAI --> AI: explanations JSON
else batch 3 (jobs 7-9)
AI -> OAI: Generate explanations
OAI --> AI: explanations JSON
else batch 4 (job 10)
AI -> OAI: Generate explanations
OAI --> AI: explanations JSON
end

AI -> PG: Persist explanations + similarity scores
activate PG
PG --> AI: saved
deactivate PG

AI -> MON: Notify match explanations generated
activate MON
MON -> FE: SignalR MatchExplanationsGenerated
deactivate MON

== Final Real-Time UX ==

FE -> GW: GET /resumes/jobs/matching
activate GW
GW -> MON: Forward request
activate MON
MON -> AI: Resolve matches
activate AI
AI -> PG: Read cached explanations + scores
activate PG
note right of PG
Cache hit — no vector recomputation.
Scores stored alongside explanations.
end note
PG --> AI: cached results
deactivate PG
AI --> MON: matches + explanations
deactivate AI
MON --> GW: 200 OK
deactivate MON
GW --> FE: Matching jobs with AI explanations
deactivate GW

note over FE
Complete user experience:
- Resume parsed progressively (~10s)
- Matches computed via pgvector
- AI explanations generated in parallel (~6s)
- All subsequent requests served from cache

No blocking. No polling. Event-driven.
end note

deactivate AI

@enduml